# Keep the portal compatible with old iPads (iOS 12 Safari) that some staff use
# as shared timeclock/manager devices. Next.js 13/14 targeted Safari 12 by
# default; Next 15+ raised the baseline to modern browsers, which stopped
# transpiling modern JS (optional chaining, nullish coalescing, etc.) down to a
# form iOS 12 Safari can parse — breaking the whole page on those devices.
# Pinning Safari/iOS 12 here restores the old, working transpile target. Modern
# browsers still run the same site fine (just a marginally larger bundle).
Chrome >= 64
Edge >= 79
Firefox >= 67
Safari >= 12
iOS >= 12
